   <titles>
      <title>Projection of a Vector onto a Line â€“ Illustration</title>
   </titles>
   <body>
      <block>
         <block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>The projection of a vector <math>
                     <latex>\Vect{x}</latex>
                  </math> in <math>
                     <latex>\RNr[n]</latex>
                  </math> onto the line through the origin in the direction of a nonzero vector <math>
                     <latex>\Vect{y}</latex>
                  </math> is defined as</para.body>
            </para>
            <math.display>
               <latex>\pr_L(\Vect{x}) = \dfrac{ \DotPr{\Vect{x}}{\Vect{y}} }{ \DotPr{\Vect{y}}{\Vect{y}} } \cdot \Vect{y}</latex>
            </math.display>
            <para>
               <para.body>The effect of this projection may be visualized as follows</para.body>
            </para>
            <media type="image" active="0" inline="0">
               <img src="ims/ProjectionVectorLine.png"/>
            </media>
            <para>
               <para.body>Shine a light vertically onto the line <math>
                     <latex>L</latex>
                  </math>. The shadow of <math>
                     <latex>\Vect{x}</latex>
                  </math> is the projection of <math>
                     <latex>\Vect{x}</latex>
                  </math> onto <math>
                     <latex>L</latex>
                  </math>. Crucial properties of this projection are:</para.body>
            </para>
            <ul>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>
                        <math>
                           <latex>\pr_{L}(\Vect{x})</latex>
                        </math> is parallel to the direction vector <math>
                           <latex>\Vect{y}</latex>
                        </math> of <math>
                           <latex>L</latex>
                        </math>.</para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>The difference vector <math>
                           <latex>\Vect{u}:= \Vect{x} - \pr_L(\Vect{x})</latex>
                        </math> is perpendicular to <math>
                           <latex>L</latex>
                        </math> and to <math>
                           <latex>\Vect{y}</latex>
                        </math>.</para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </block.body>
      </block>
   </body>
